reviewText: I had a copy of this before, but lost it.  Now I'm buying the DVD and I'm looking forward to seeing it again.  This movie is nothing short of hilarious.  I really can't explain on here.  Some of the things that these guys do is just too out there to be written down.  You really have to see it for yourself.  Watching it over and over is one thing.  However, showing it to your friends is worth the price of the disc.  nuff said.one more thing.  If you watch this, you're going to want to buy CKY's album.  The music and the movie go hand in hand.

reviewText: This movie is a sequal to the original CKY (Camp Kill Yourself) video from the mind of Bam Margera and friends.  Its got everything from gross stuff (like the poo prank...) and skateboarding stuff.  Some stuff seems so dangerous you wonder why they do it, but its interesting (and I mean really interesting) to watch.  I highly recommend this movie, and the CKY album if you feel like spending the 10 to 15 bucks extra, which I would if I had cash...

reviewText: Okay. There it is within the realm of possibility that a comedy troupe could come along and create a series that is the funniest for a certain demographic (conservative Baby Boomers will despise it). This is that comedy troupe. Camp Kill Yourself, led by the outrageous pro skater Bam Margera, is a serious gang of idiots.There are scenes in this movie that are painfully hilarious, and each one makes you wonder how they got away with it, while retaining their liberty. Augmented by pop music, the skits are fast-paced and only meant to be stupid and funny. If you watch this movie when you are inebriated or extremely tired, it will seem all that much funnier.This movie was so funny, that MTV hired them to do their own TV show, called Jackass. But this movie is completely uncut, and the DVD offers TWICE the good stuff that the VHS has. If you even remotely like skating, are male, and under the age of 28, you will like this movie. Unless you dont know how to laugh, of course.No guy should go to college without this video, it will score major points in the dorm.
summary: The laughter gave brought me to tears! TOO Funny!

reviewText: All I have to say is GET THIS! Get it now. You will laugh as hard as possible. Plus it has great skating from Bam and friends. You will see Bam Margera, Jess Margera, Rake Yohn, Mike Maldonado, Raab Himself, Leo Fitzpatrick (yes of kids fame), Kerry "Hockey Temper" Getz, and alot others. Just pick it up. Also pick up cky landspeed (the first one), and remember to pick up CKY3. This is kinda like Jackass but without all the stupid MTV censoring..
